About
=================================

This is a temporal package to provide configuration and some data to fix issues
when generating DVIs/PDFs from tex sources in Japanese.



Files
=================================

etc/fonts/conf.d/90-texlive-local.conf
---------------------------------------------------

A fontconfig configuration file to display output Japanese PDF files in which
Japanese (IPA-ex gothic and mincho) fonts are not embedded.


usr/bin/tex2pdf
-------------------------------------------

Platex (texlive-east-asian) looks not able to process TeX sources in UTF-8, so
the sources need to be converted from UTF-8 to EUC-JP.

Along with that, you have to call platex and dvipdfmx to generate PDF outputs
from TeX sources with font map configuration specified with -f option to
embed Japanese truetype fonts.

This simple script is an wrapper for platex, dvipdfmx, iconv, etc and hides
messy affairs like above.


usr/share/texmf/web2c/texmf.cnf
-------------------------------------------

SEE ALSO: RHBZ#736242 (https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=736242)


etc/texmf/dvipdfmx/ipaex.map
---------------------------------------------------

Fonts map configuration to embedded IPA-ex truetype fonts in output PDF files
generated by dvipdfmx.



Build & Install
=================================

1. autoreconf -vfi
2. ./configure
3. make 
4. make srpm
5. mock /path/to/built/*.src.rpm


